00:41:02,900 --> 00:41:05,440
[Seo Boseok: Because that moment
isn't far away now.]

1488
00:41:05,800 --> 00:41:09,540
[Min Sungwoo: When fans chant “Min Sungwoo,”]

1489
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:13,490
[Min Sungwoo: and sing the cheer song,
that's when I feel happiest.]

1490
00:41:13,810 --> 00:41:17,320
[Jin Hyunwoo: When I run with my friends
and look at Jamsil Stadium,]

1491
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:20,750
[Jin Hyunwoo: I've shouted toward it many times.]

1492
00:41:20,750 --> 00:41:23,230
[Jin Hyunwoo: Please, just give me one chance—
even if you discard me after.]

1493
00:41:23,820 --> 00:41:26,250
[Just let me play once.]

1494
00:41:26,490 --> 00:41:30,240
[I'm begging you, just let me stand
on the mound and throw one pitch…!]

1495
00:41:28,860 --> 00:41:30,590
Even one pitch would be enough.

1496
00:41:30,770 --> 00:41:33,770
[With a burning passion for baseball,]

1497
00:41:30,980 --> 00:41:33,780
I've shouted like that many times with my friends.

1498
00:41:33,840 --> 00:41:36,620
[Standing in that spot all along. Source: team]

1499
00:41:37,130 --> 00:41:39,540
[With unwavering determination. Source: team]

1500
00:41:40,100 --> 00:41:42,600
[The days of chasing a dream. Source: team]

1501
00:41:43,180 --> 00:41:46,190
[Going through the independent league
that once felt like the end. Source: team]

1502
00:41:47,390 --> 00:41:51,830
[A professional dream achieved after 20 years]

1503
00:41:48,480 --> 00:41:49,780
Okay, okay, okay.

1504
00:41:51,540 --> 00:41:52,880
That's great—keep it up.

1505
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:55,630
[The Ulsan dark horse team,
united by their ambitions]

1506
00:41:55,750 --> 00:41:56,250
Hello, everyone.

1507
00:41:56,150 --> 00:41:59,820
[Min Sungwoo, catcher. A player with
determination, now at his last chance]

1508
00:41:56,310 --> 00:41:59,900
I'm Min Sungwoo, and I joined as a catcher.

1509
00:42:00,130 --> 00:42:03,950
[It took 3 years to return to the field]

1510
00:42:00,160 --> 00:42:01,570
-Over those 3 years...
-Yes.

1511
00:42:01,570 --> 00:42:03,230
What did you do?

1512
00:42:04,330 --> 00:42:06,420
[Min Sungwoo: I first joined a pro team
and stayed about a year.]

1513
00:42:06,420 --> 00:42:07,860
[Min Sungwoo: Then in my second year,
I went to the military.]

1514
00:42:08,260 --> 00:42:09,990
[Min Sungwoo: During that time,
I heard I was released.]

1515
00:42:09,990 --> 00:42:13,280
[At the moment of wanting to give up,
unnoticed. Source: team.]

1516
00:42:10,200 --> 00:42:12,590
At one point, I considered quitting baseball.

1517
00:42:12,590 --> 00:42:14,830
But later, I decided to work
as a bullpen catcher while—

1518
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:16,550
[Min Sungwoo: I worked as a bullpen catcher
while challenging again to become a pro…]

1519
00:42:16,950 --> 00:42:19,470
[Reigniting my passion for baseball]

1520
00:42:17,150 --> 00:42:19,410
In the end, the team readily accepted me.

1521
00:42:19,600 --> 00:42:21,790
Until last year, I was still a bullpen catcher.

1522
00:42:19,700 --> 00:42:22,300
[The result of quietly
working hard off the field]

1523
00:42:22,070 --> 00:42:24,540
Now I can finally return as a player again.

1524
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:26,970
[Officially joining the Ulsan Whales
professional team]

1525
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:26,290
When I passed,

1526
00:42:27,720 --> 00:42:31,180
[Min Sungwoo: (Upon hearing I passed),
at first, I thought it was a trick.]

1527
00:42:29,700 --> 00:42:31,100
But after they showed me,

1528
00:42:32,820 --> 00:42:35,590
[Min Sungwoo: I couldn't hold it in
and burst into tears on the spot.]

1529
00:42:37,100 --> 00:42:37,870
Sorry.

1530
00:42:40,610 --> 00:42:44,120
I guess those were tears of gratitude.

1531
00:42:42,810 --> 00:42:49,600
[Tears of gratitude: “Because
I can play baseball again.”]

1532
00:42:45,470 --> 00:42:47,400
Because I can play baseball again.

1533
00:42:49,590 --> 00:42:50,520
That's how it felt.

1534
00:42:50,400 --> 00:42:52,500
[Min Sungwoo: Like a huge weight was lifted?]

1535
00:42:52,500 --> 00:42:56,440
[Min Sungwoo: And I'm grateful
to my parents for bringing me this far…]

1536
00:42:58,410 --> 00:42:59,090
Sorry.

1537
00:42:59,710 --> 00:43:02,570
[Precious tears that bear
witness to this journey]

1538
00:43:02,570 --> 00:43:08,630
[An opportunity he created
through relentless effort. Source: team]

1539
00:43:03,780 --> 00:43:04,880
Okay, very good.

1540
00:43:09,590 --> 00:43:13,050
[Min Sungwoo: I hadn't played
in a game for nearly 3 years.]

1541
00:43:13,050 --> 00:43:16,100
[Min Sungwoo: During that time,
my desire for baseball only grew stronger.]

1542
00:43:16,600 --> 00:43:19,790
[Min Sungwoo: Being able to stand on the field
again now makes me very happy.]

1543
00:43:20,030 --> 00:43:22,620
And every morning when
I come to work, I always feel—

1544
00:43:20,220 --> 00:43:25,730
[Every morning, I feel excited inside]

1545
00:43:22,670 --> 00:43:25,140
This sense of excitement.

1546
00:43:26,170 --> 00:43:29,700
[Looks like you truly love baseball.]

1547
00:43:30,020 --> 00:43:32,470
[Final question after careful thought]

1548
00:43:32,870 --> 00:43:35,390
So, what does baseball mean to you?

1549
00:43:32,980 --> 00:43:39,380
[Q. What does baseball mean to you?]

1550
00:43:35,740 --> 00:43:37,470
To me, baseball is first of all—

1551
00:43:41,740 --> 00:43:44,080
it's my life.

1552
00:43:42,640 --> 00:43:49,140
[Baseball is both my life
and everything to me.]

1553
00:43:44,730 --> 00:43:46,260
It's everything in my life.

1554
00:43:47,290 --> 00:43:50,090
Even though I know I still
have many shortcomings,

1555
00:43:50,640 --> 00:43:53,460
[I will strive to become
an indispensable role player.]

1556
00:43:53,940 --> 00:43:55,070
Alright, thank you.

1557
00:43:55,160 --> 00:43:56,030
Thank you.

1558
00:43:56,190 --> 00:43:57,130
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

1559
00:43:57,130 --> 00:43:58,670
-Thank you, sir.
-Thank you.

1560
00:43:57,240 --> 00:44:01,380
[The players' sincerity is fully
conveyed to their Manitos]

1561
00:43:58,720 --> 00:43:59,890
-Fighting!
-Fighting!

1562
00:43:59,890 --> 00:44:00,530
Fighting!

1563
00:44:01,690 --> 00:44:04,220
[To me, baseball means—]

1564
00:44:01,710 --> 00:44:02,500
Baseball is—

1565
00:44:04,410 --> 00:44:06,660
it's everything in my life.

1566
00:44:04,610 --> 00:44:06,740
[Everything in my life.]

1567
00:44:06,980 --> 00:44:08,960
[A textbook of life.]

1568
00:44:09,270 --> 00:44:11,920
Maybe it's proof
that I've lived with all my effort.

1569
00:44:09,350 --> 00:44:12,290
[Proof of a life lived with effort.]

1570
00:44:12,600 --> 00:44:16,320
[Feels like I've married baseball—
I love baseball.]

1571
00:44:12,660 --> 00:44:14,790
Because I truly love baseball itself,

1572
00:44:14,820 --> 00:44:16,530
it feels like I've married baseball.

1573
00:44:16,530 --> 00:44:18,130
[In the process of "working hard,"]

1574
00:44:18,130 --> 00:44:19,750
[I learned how to pour out sweat,]

1575
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:22,640
[and how to overcome failure.]

1576
00:44:22,870 --> 00:44:26,890
[Namho: So choosing baseball
was probably the best decision I've ever made!]

1577
00:44:26,260 --> 00:44:27,060
That's right.

1578
00:44:28,260 --> 00:44:31,630
[Looking at the field, firm in his belief]

1579
00:44:32,490 --> 00:44:35,750
[I want to chase even bigger dreams.]

1580
00:44:36,070 --> 00:44:39,380
It's because I have goals and dreams
that I've made it this far.

1581
00:44:36,370 --> 00:44:39,170
[It's because of dreams that I can keep going.]

1582
00:44:39,400 --> 00:44:41,160
[It makes me truly feel that I'm alive.]

1583
00:44:41,160 --> 00:44:42,930
[I'm really happy, and I feel blessed.]

1584
00:44:42,930 --> 00:44:46,200
[I want to devote even more energy to baseball.]

1585
00:44:45,310 --> 00:44:46,910
This is the future I dream of.

1586
00:44:49,120 --> 00:44:53,090
[After meeting the players,
you can feel their passion]

1587
00:44:54,140 --> 00:44:55,130
Are we off work now?

1588
00:44:54,180 --> 00:44:57,270
[Whale TV Group off work]

1589
00:44:57,720 --> 00:45:00,680
[Cha Taehyun: Let's stop here—
I'm too nervous, I can't go on.]

1590
00:44:59,430 --> 00:45:00,270
Yeah.

1591
00:45:01,050 --> 00:45:02,900
[Uh… please let me take it off.]

1592
00:45:02,940 --> 00:45:03,890
Good work.

1593
00:45:03,170 --> 00:45:06,610
[Boyoung Whale, active in every way]

1594
00:45:04,680 --> 00:45:06,340
The interview was really great.

1595
00:45:06,340 --> 00:45:07,700
What baseball means to me—

1596
00:45:07,230 --> 00:45:10,240
[“What does baseball mean to me?”
Boyoung's ambitious question]

1597
00:45:07,950 --> 00:45:09,910
-“What does baseball mean to me?” That's not easy.
-Because I...

1598
00:45:09,910 --> 00:45:10,560
What baseball means to me—

1599
00:45:10,510 --> 00:45:14,550
[Park Boyoung: This is the question I struggle
with
the most when promoting my work.]

1600
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:15,290
What does acting mean to me?

1601
00:45:15,290 --> 00:45:18,920
[Park Boyoung: “What does acting mean to me?”
“What does this work mean to me?”]

1602
00:45:18,920 --> 00:45:21,460
[Park Boyoung: Questions like these
really get you thinking.]

1603
00:45:20,100 --> 00:45:20,970
Right, right.

1604
00:45:21,110 --> 00:45:24,210
But for the players, it feels different.

1605
00:45:22,970 --> 00:45:26,300
[A meaningful question for the players right now]

1606
00:45:24,420 --> 00:45:25,550
You did really well.

1607
00:45:25,680 --> 00:45:26,400
Really.

1608
00:45:26,470 --> 00:45:28,020
[Well, but honestly—]

1609
00:45:26,540 --> 00:45:29,520
But I feel like,
with them sitting right next to me,

1610
00:45:28,250 --> 00:45:31,000
[Park Boyoung: With them sitting next
to me like this, this perspective—]

1611
00:45:29,640 --> 00:45:34,180
From this angle,
I can clearly see their eyes.

1612
00:45:31,550 --> 00:45:34,920
[Seeing the players' eyes right in front of me]

1613
00:45:34,750 --> 00:45:37,650
They're so bright.

1614
00:45:35,670 --> 00:45:40,080
[Those sparkling, lively eyes]

1615
00:45:37,800 --> 00:45:39,550
So full of life.

1616
00:45:40,060 --> 00:45:41,660
They're completely immersed.

1617
00:45:40,230 --> 00:45:43,500
[Moved by their passion]

1618
00:45:42,170 --> 00:45:43,080
Exactly.

1619
00:45:43,630 --> 00:45:45,960
-Their determination really stands out.
-Right.

1620
00:45:43,670 --> 00:45:46,090
[Park Boyoung: Their determination
really stands out.]

1621
00:45:46,510 --> 00:45:49,070
[Park Boyoung: They truly love baseball.]

1622
00:45:49,370 --> 00:45:52,500
[Cha Taehyun: Just being able
to play makes them happy.]

1623
00:45:52,500 --> 00:45:55,310
-Please show them lots of support.
-That's right.

1624
00:45:52,880 --> 00:45:58,490
[After the interviews, the urge
to cheer grew even stronger]

1625
00:45:55,440 --> 00:45:57,840
-We really have to do this now.
-Seriously.

1626
00:45:58,990 --> 00:46:02,900
Hope everyone likes the support song tomorrow.

1627
00:45:59,110 --> 00:46:03,120
[Tomorrow everyone's been waiting for—
hope they like the support surprise too!]

1628
00:46:03,370 --> 00:46:05,640
[But what if…]

1629
00:46:06,590 --> 00:46:11,050
[If our faces show on the big screen
during the surprise]

1630
00:46:08,610 --> 00:46:11,230
We can't let people see our faces, right?

1631
00:46:11,370 --> 00:46:13,620
[Director Cha is struggling with it too]

1632
00:46:11,370 --> 00:46:13,420
-I'm thinking about that.
-Really?

1633
00:46:13,590 --> 00:46:16,120
We could make it a live stream—if we're filmed,
it'll go on the big screen anyway.

1634
00:46:13,890 --> 00:46:19,940
[Like a kiss cam moment?
A support idea: big screen surprise + live reveal!]

1635
00:46:16,340 --> 00:46:17,160
-Show up via live stream.
-Like when you go to a baseball game...

1636
00:46:17,160 --> 00:46:18,290
Just like a kiss cam.

1637
00:46:18,300 --> 00:46:20,940
-Right, right—the kiss cam...
-It shows up on the big screen.

1638
00:46:20,940 --> 00:46:23,700
We made banners and even a fight song.

1639
00:46:23,890 --> 00:46:27,450
-Aside from the citizen interviews—
-We've done everything.

1640
00:46:24,030 --> 00:46:27,530
[By the way, how's
the citizen interview team going?]

1641
00:46:27,650 --> 00:46:30,460
-Can they pull it off?
-It's the weekend, lots of people at the mall.

1642
00:46:27,940 --> 00:46:31,490
[Meanwhile, the trio arrives in downtown Ulsan]

1643
00:46:30,710 --> 00:46:32,010
So I'm planning to interview people here.

1644
00:46:31,880 --> 00:46:34,290
[Hwang Kwanghee: I prepared
interview questions on the way here.]

1645
00:46:34,290 --> 00:46:35,840
[Hwang Kwanghee: I wrote everything down.]

1646
00:46:35,580 --> 00:46:37,090
I jotted down some keywords.

1647
00:46:35,950 --> 00:46:38,390
[Cheat sheet written right on his palm]

1648
00:46:37,310 --> 00:46:38,400
So I'm not worried.

1649
00:46:38,610 --> 00:46:40,060
[Oh, okay, nice!]

1650
00:46:39,550 --> 00:46:41,590
Let's go in later—
there are 2 people here.

1651
00:46:40,600 --> 00:46:43,260
[Super fast negotiation completed]

1652
00:46:41,720 --> 00:46:43,420
I'll do the interview—come here.

1653
00:46:43,420 --> 00:46:45,220
[Hwang Kwanghee: Do you know
Ulsan has a citizen baseball team?]

1654
00:46:45,340 --> 00:46:46,380
-Yes.
-Is it the newly formed one?

1655
00:46:45,440 --> 00:46:47,410
[Is it the newly formed one?]

1656
00:46:46,520 --> 00:46:47,340
-Do you know it?
-Yes.

1657
00:46:47,340 --> 00:46:47,980
1, 2, 3—

1658
00:46:48,150 --> 00:46:49,270
-Ulsan Whales.
-Ulsan Whales.

1659
00:46:48,210 --> 00:46:50,090
[Ulsan Whales!]

1660
00:46:49,410 --> 00:46:50,110
Nice.

1661
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:51,810
I don't even need to interview anymore.

1662
00:46:50,260 --> 00:46:51,910
[Guess they're pretty well-known]

1663
00:46:51,820 --> 00:46:53,150
What's my latest work?

1664
00:46:52,040 --> 00:46:53,260
[Am I famous too?]

1665
00:46:53,410 --> 00:46:54,360
[“The Negotiation King”?]

1666
00:46:54,420 --> 00:46:55,910
[That was like 3 years ago…]

1667
00:46:56,100 --> 00:46:57,430
[Now I should promote myself—
who else would I promote…]

1668
00:46:57,560 --> 00:47:00,560
[(Today's “Support King”)
Say something to cheer on the Ulsan Whales!]

1669
00:47:00,900 --> 00:47:04,310
[To the Ulsan Whales players:
Hey! Guys, you can do it!]

1670
00:47:03,150 --> 00:47:06,090
I made it—you guys
can do it too. Fighting!

1671
00:47:04,440 --> 00:47:07,180
[Fighting! Fighting!]

1672
00:47:07,390 --> 00:47:09,810
[Oh, okay—shall we take a photo?]

1673
00:47:10,050 --> 00:47:11,030
[What do you think of me in person?]

1674
00:47:11,140 --> 00:47:12,040
[So handsome!]

1675
00:47:12,170 --> 00:47:13,080
[Really?]

1676
00:47:12,480 --> 00:47:13,220
-Really.
-So handsome.

1677
00:47:13,190 --> 00:47:14,850
[Citizens: So handsome]

1678
00:47:13,350 --> 00:47:17,260
-So handsome.
-I'm so popular—this is amazing.

1679
00:47:15,060 --> 00:47:17,610
[So popular—so happy!]

1680
00:47:17,900 --> 00:47:20,340
[Let's take it—okay. Take all my love!]

1681
00:47:20,400 --> 00:47:21,280
Cheek heart.

1682
00:47:20,530 --> 00:47:24,590
[The support king in his element]

1683
00:47:21,460 --> 00:47:22,850
Hello.

1684
00:47:23,100 --> 00:47:24,210
I'm so happy.

1685
00:47:24,770 --> 00:47:25,770
[Hello]

1686
00:47:26,650 --> 00:47:28,360
[Do you want to chat with me?]

1687
00:47:27,750 --> 00:47:28,520
Mm.

1688
00:47:28,510 --> 00:47:30,150
[Hello. Hello!]

1689
00:47:29,240 --> 00:47:30,240
Hello, come here.

1690
00:47:30,810 --> 00:47:31,650
Come here.

1691
00:47:32,220 --> 00:47:34,350
[Hwang Kwanghee: Nice to meet you.
Please introduce yourself!]

1692
00:47:34,590 --> 00:47:35,840
I'm in fourth grade.

1693
00:47:34,800 --> 00:47:36,990
[Fourth grade… Class 1.]

1694
00:47:35,950 --> 00:47:37,030
No, fourth grade Class 1.

1695
00:47:37,030 --> 00:47:37,550
You.

1696
00:47:37,100 --> 00:47:39,800
[Mom, I don't have a class.] [Hahaha.]

1697
00:47:39,700 --> 00:47:41,270
-You're not in school yet?
-Kindergarten.

1698
00:47:40,530 --> 00:47:41,150
[Kindergarten x3]

1699
00:47:41,560 --> 00:47:43,590
[Restart! Okay, be steady!]

1700
00:47:41,610 --> 00:47:43,500
Start—stay steady.

1701
00:47:43,730 --> 00:47:46,550
[Hello, I'm Kang Yeseo from OO Kindergarten.]

1702
00:47:46,940 --> 00:47:49,810
[A lovely family from Ulsan]

1703
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:47,970
Nice to meet you.

1704
00:47:48,100 --> 00:47:49,030
Are you a family?

1705
00:47:49,060 --> 00:47:49,840
Yes.

1706
00:47:50,070 --> 00:47:53,190
[Hwang Kwanghee: How did Mom and Unnie support you, Yeseo?]

1707
00:47:53,860 --> 00:47:54,750
[What?]

1708
00:47:54,880 --> 00:47:56,890
[Hwang Kwanghee: Have they ever supported you?] [No]

1709
00:47:57,070 --> 00:47:58,670
[Mom is flustered]

1710
00:47:57,790 --> 00:47:58,820
Wait, how did this happen?

1711
00:47:58,820 --> 00:48:01,250
[Hwang Kwanghee: Have they ever told you, "You're a good girl, Yeseo"?]
[A firm no]

1712
00:48:01,440 --> 00:48:03,080
[Mom...] [Oh... Mm-hmm... Yeseo...]

1713
00:48:03,190 --> 00:48:04,080
[You never told me that]

1714
00:48:05,440 --> 00:48:06,380
[I'll just say it now]

1715
00:48:06,680 --> 00:48:08,780
[Go for it! I love you!]

1716
00:48:07,580 --> 00:48:08,840
You never told me that.

1717
00:48:09,010 --> 00:48:10,480
[Has Mom ever told you that, Yeonseo?]

1718
00:48:10,650 --> 00:48:12,260
[Well... Yeah...]

1719
00:48:12,510 --> 00:48:16,000
[I'll just say it now. I love you!]

1720
00:48:12,560 --> 00:48:14,530
Yeseo, Yeonseo. I love you.

1721
00:48:14,670 --> 00:48:15,530
I love you.

1722
00:48:15,810 --> 00:48:16,490
Go!

1723
00:48:16,700 --> 00:48:19,190
Go, Ulsan Whales players!

1724
00:48:16,800 --> 00:48:19,890
[Go, Ulsan Whales!]

1725
00:48:19,320 --> 00:48:20,080
Thank you.

